Guidelines Purpose How it will be addressed 
General Data 
Protection 
Act GDPR 
2016 
Ensure personal data is 
protected and not used for 
malicious means 
All personal data collected by the website will only be 
relevant to the functionality of the website, no personal data 
will be kept for longer than it needs to be, for example if a 
user deletes their account and the user will be able to have 
access to their data to ensure that it is up-to-date 
Equality act 
of 2010 
Prevent discrimination and 
ensure inclusivity 
Accepting a terms of service once signing up to the website 
that states the user is not allowed to discriminate against 
anyone whilst using the site 
WCAG 2.0 Ensures a shared standard 
for accessibility that meets 
the needs of anyone 
regardless of their ability 
Users will be able to change how the website is displayed for 
them through a settings menu that will provide many 
features designed to make the site more accessible. There 
will also be alt-text provided for any image so users who use 
text-to-speech will still be able to use the service. 
